Kotlin Web Demo is a web-based application capable of editing/running Kotlin code in the browser: http://kotlin-demo.jetbrains.com

0)Create MySql database
1)Build ant target init
2)Open project in Idea and set correct path for the tomcat in Edit Configurations tab
3)Create context file in kotlin.web.demo.server/web/META_INF

Context variables:
java_home(optimal)
java_execute(optimal)
app_home(optimal)
auth_redirect(required)
is_test_version(required)
(google/twitter/facebook)_key(required)
(google/twitter/facebook)_secret(required)

Also database connection properties must be specified in context like this:
<Resource type="javax.sql.DataSource" name="jdbc/kotlin" factory="org.apache.tomcat.dbcp.dbcp.BasicDataSourceFactory"
 url="URL" driverClassName="com.mysql.jdbc.Driver" password="PASSWORD" username="USERNAME" auth="Container"/>
